The way I understand this request, it is to get us, as you've presented, into the door and to have items for discussion on the table for us to see what can be funded and what we can receive help with.

1026
01:21:32,561 --> 01:21:37,324
I'm all in favor of a priority list from the school board.

1027
01:21:38,224 --> 01:21:42,327
My concern with priority lists from anybody is that they be responsible.

1028
01:21:43,119 --> 01:21:55,584
and that they have in mind a larger picture that though this body makes the final decision that we all share a responsibility in.

1029
01:21:57,165 --> 01:22:01,727
I approve of this request and I will support it, Mr. Superintendent.

1030
01:22:02,267 --> 01:22:08,230
I must say that I hope that when we get into further discussion on how or

1031
01:22:09,048 --> 01:22:23,212
in what way some of this money and some of these grants might be directed that we're able to address some of the money that we've spent in the past on the same thing several times.

1032
01:22:24,752 --> 01:22:34,475
It seems as though we're chasing leaks in those roofs and replacing them and spending hundreds of thousands of dollars on those roofs in a frequent manner.

1033
01:22:35,063 --> 01:22:39,646
I'm concerned about that, and I hope we can get to the bottom of the top of the building.

1034
01:22:40,446 --> 01:22:45,869
And so, I think I've said enough, and I think perhaps we've heard enough tonight.

1035
01:22:46,490 --> 01:22:49,411
And so, I'd like to move approval, Mr. President.

1036
01:22:49,651 --> 01:22:50,352
Thank you.

1037
01:22:50,572 --> 01:22:53,233
Mr. President, just one quick thing to Councilor, if I may.

1038
01:22:54,114 --> 01:22:56,715
Just that we did an infrared study of the high school roof.

1039
01:22:57,656 --> 01:23:02,319
We will repair those things that need to be repaired for about $25,000 this summer.

1040
01:23:03,099 --> 01:23:03,379
Okay?

1041
01:23:03,419 --> 01:23:04,400
That's about all we need to do.

1042
01:23:05,078 --> 01:23:14,562
The long-term renovation or repair or reconstruction of the roof is five to six years out, and, you know, if we were to take it to the end.

1043
01:23:14,642 --> 01:23:16,123
So that's really where we're at.

1044
01:23:16,823 --> 01:23:28,528
We had a couple of very difficult snow periods a few years ago where shoveling was required on the roof to avoid collapse and the like that may have done some damage in certain areas, and we need to repair those.

1045
01:23:28,568 --> 01:23:30,849
But other than that, the roof's got another five, six years.

1046
01:23:31,429 --> 01:23:31,669
Thank you.

1047
01:23:32,990 --> 01:23:33,710
Council Member Kern.

1048
01:23:34,876 --> 01:23:37,697
Mr. Caviello, through the chair, I just want to ask for clarification.

1049
01:23:37,777 --> 01:23:43,400
So we're asking for a priority list and we're asking, I mean, I guess it would be a good compromise.

1050
01:23:43,480 --> 01:23:48,482
Are we asking to keep the document as is and then put the priority list in there?

1051
01:23:48,582 --> 01:23:49,842
Did you state that Councilor Marks?

1052
01:23:50,323 --> 01:23:52,184
Put the priority list within the application?

1053
01:23:57,486 --> 01:23:59,667
I thought I heard you say that it will be within the document.

1054
01:24:00,547 --> 01:24:04,309
We could put in the document or the superintendent says he sits down and meets with the state.

1055
01:24:05,203 --> 01:24:07,364
I have no problem with him presenting the priority list.

1056
01:24:08,464 --> 01:24:12,105
So it doesn't, I don't care about the avenue it gets to the state.

1057
01:24:13,145 --> 01:24:13,405
Okay.

1058
01:24:13,445 --> 01:24:13,706
Yeah.

1059
01:24:13,806 --> 01:24:28,870
I just wouldn't make like to add that, that our priority list that is drafted within the next week or two, even be added as a, an attachment to the application so that the state knows, yes, we're looking for everything, but these are our top

1060
01:24:29,597 --> 01:24:36,622
whatever it might be, 10, 11, 12 things that we need done within the next five to 10 years that we're going to be putting money forward anyway for.

1061
01:24:36,642 --> 01:24:40,184
And we would love some state reimbursement.

1062
01:24:40,304 --> 01:24:42,385
I think that I'd just like to add that to the paper.

1063
01:24:43,166 --> 01:24:48,289
And I'd also like to just point out that I think I heard that this document maybe was produced in September.

1064
01:24:48,789 --> 01:24:53,753
And I think the school committee voted on it on the 6th of February, which was a month and a half ago.

1065
01:24:53,773 --> 01:24:58,976
And for some reason, it came before us tonight with only a week or two left before it's actually due.

1066
01:24:59,598 --> 01:25:10,022
So in the future, it would be nice to, obviously the school committee has the right to review and to discuss first, but a little bit sooner so that maybe we could prepare a little bit more.

1067
01:25:10,042 --> 01:25:11,063
We got it on Friday.

1068
01:25:11,083 --> 01:25:20,526
I think a lot of us review our packet over the weekend, leaving us only a couple of days to form questions, do research, make calls, and get the questions we want answered before we have to vote on it.

1069
01:25:20,587 --> 01:25:28,990
And it always just feels, no offense to the superintendent, but no matter what we're presented, half the time, especially if it's something important, we're giving it

1070
01:25:29,582 --> 01:25:45,367
the week of and it's just not the right way to run a city and to be transparent with not only us as the people who are elected to make the votes but to the people who are electing us who are going to come and ask us the questions or who ask us the questions after they hear the meeting.

1071
01:25:46,047 --> 01:25:58,551
So I think just think in the future and I'll say that all the time and whether or not it happens, highly unlikely, but I think it's extremely important to be more transparent and to give the city council more time for review.

1072
01:25:59,093 --> 01:25:59,373
Thank you.

1073
01:25:59,473 --> 01:26:01,514
So, Mr. President, if I could just respond.

1074
01:26:01,755 --> 01:26:02,955
I mean, I feel I have to.

1075
01:26:03,496 --> 01:26:06,277
The document you're referring to in September was a different document.

1076
01:26:06,417 --> 01:26:19,365
That's the capital plan that came from the mayor, which through the school committee, the document you have in front of you was approved by the school committee on February 6th after a committee, the whole meeting that they had the week before on that.

1077
01:26:19,846 --> 01:26:22,267
And you received it, what do you call it tonight?

1078
01:26:23,428 --> 01:26:24,569
Uh, because what do you call it?

1079
01:26:24,589 --> 01:26:26,810
You were busy dealing with other capital

1080
01:26:27,412 --> 01:26:31,753
considerations, in particular the police station and other things like that, so that we didn't confuse those two items.

1081
01:26:31,813 --> 01:26:35,134
But the reality is that that's the two things.

1082
01:26:35,174 --> 01:26:39,176
And the other point I guess I would make is that the state has a form.

1083
01:26:39,596 --> 01:26:40,636
We filled out the form.

1084
01:26:41,016 --> 01:26:42,817
You don't add to the form.

1085
01:26:42,877 --> 01:26:45,617
We'll be happy to provide that priority list to them.

1086
01:26:46,378 --> 01:26:47,518
But the form is the form.

1087
01:26:47,538 --> 01:26:48,398
That's what you submit.

1088
01:26:48,959 --> 01:26:52,620
You don't add things to an application that is not required.

1089
01:26:52,660 --> 01:26:57,181
I think that would be not consistent with the way you make a submittal.

1090
01:26:57,984 --> 01:27:11,107
Um, so, but certainly we respect the right, you know, that the council has asked and we've certainly will honor that to come up with a priority list, provide it to you and provide it to MSBA as part of the discussions that take place.

1091
01:27:11,767 --> 01:27:12,107
Thank you.

1092
01:27:12,187 --> 01:27:13,167
Councilor Del Rosso.

1093
01:27:13,427 --> 01:27:25,330
I would, uh, my point was to be, uh, in support of that priority list attachment in so much as it, uh, it doesn't act as a hindrance or as an appropriate in that forum.

1094
01:27:26,035 --> 01:27:38,725
I, uh, trust that the superintendent, uh, through the process of meetings, uh, with the authority and, uh, his presence and his negotiating skills won't lead us to be bamboozled.

1095
01:27:39,906 --> 01:27:40,266
Thank you.

1096
01:27:40,326 --> 01:27:44,089
Counselor Dela Rosa and Mr. Superintendent, I thank you for your leadership.

1097
01:27:44,510 --> 01:27:50,515
Our technical school and high school has moved forward on the last few years under your guidance and I hope to see it continue moving forward.

1098
01:27:50,595 --> 01:27:50,995
Thank you.

1099
01:27:51,095 --> 01:27:51,415
Thank you.

1100
01:27:52,016 --> 01:27:54,418
I think we have somebody that wants to speak and back me up.

1101
01:27:54,558 --> 01:27:54,738
Okay.

1102
01:27:57,223 --> 01:27:59,424
Excuse me, Mr. Penta, the gentleman was first.

1103
01:28:03,446 --> 01:28:04,487
Name and address of the record, please.

1104
01:28:04,987 --> 01:28:06,728
David McKillop, 94 Rock Glen Road.

1105
01:28:07,849 --> 01:28:10,450
I was listening to all the conversation tonight.

1106
01:28:10,610 --> 01:28:15,333
And I guess being a business person, I'm all about planning.

1107
01:28:15,933 --> 01:28:19,175
And it seems to be that for whatever reason, we're struggling with planning.

1108
01:28:20,176 --> 01:28:23,557
One of the things that really strikes me as curious is the MSBA.

1109
01:28:24,998 --> 01:28:26,359
The MSBA was presented.

1110
01:28:26,708 --> 01:28:29,029
Now, when it was presented is the question.

1111
01:28:29,269 --> 01:28:38,352
Because if it was presented two months ago, six months ago, a year ago, then you may have had the opportunity to actually get more information a lot sooner.

1112
01:28:38,372 --> 01:28:39,953
So that should be a question that should be asked.

1113
01:28:40,493 --> 01:28:44,855
When is the MSBA turn around and say, hey, when does the door open?

1114
01:28:45,815 --> 01:28:48,116
Mr. Subutani, can you answer the gentleman's question?

1115
01:28:50,177 --> 01:28:55,519
The MSBA opens up a window for statements of interest in January.

1116
01:28:56,115 --> 01:29:00,078
and then expects it to follow through by the April date.

1117
01:29:00,438 --> 01:29:02,000
They actually pushed it out a little bit this year.

1118
01:29:02,040 --> 01:29:02,920
Normally it's in March.

1119
01:29:03,341 --> 01:29:05,963
But they open up the window for the SOIs in January.

1120
01:29:06,744 --> 01:29:06,844
OK.

1121
01:29:06,904 --> 01:29:07,244
Thank you.

1122
01:29:07,564 --> 01:29:08,485
So that's the first thing.

1123
01:29:08,858 --> 01:29:18,647
So if it's being opened up in January, the meeting is being done in February, the finalization is then, now it's March, April, really the window is much, much smaller than you might actually anticipate.

1124
01:29:18,688 --> 01:29:21,730
So the question isn't answered in the respect of how to plan this better.

1125
01:29:22,211 --> 01:29:29,038
So now to be proactive, the next time the MSBA opens up, I think as a city council, I personally,

1126
01:29:29,858 --> 01:29:37,704
if it were me, would say, hey, the next time this opens, we want from day one to know when and how and what we need to do.

1127
01:29:38,064 --> 01:29:39,105
We want to be part of that.

1128
01:29:39,525 --> 01:29:47,591
So when the school committee goes into the committee of the whole, the discussion is made, you're already aware something's going to be coming to your desk.

1129
01:29:47,651 --> 01:29:48,572
And I think that would help.

1130
01:29:49,392 --> 01:29:55,817
To me, again, looking at a business perspective, I've been in business for 14 years.

1131
01:29:57,655 --> 01:29:59,656
Business needs a facelift, really, really bad.

1132
01:29:59,896 --> 01:30:02,058
So if you guys want to help me with that, please contribute.

1133
01:30:02,938 --> 01:30:08,782
But in order to do that, four years ago, I had to start planning for this coming year, not 2017, 2018.

1134
01:30:11,324 --> 01:30:13,365
Four years ago, I started to put that plan together.

1135
01:30:13,425 --> 01:30:15,526
Four years ago, I did a cost analysis.

1136
01:30:15,626 --> 01:30:20,749
Four years ago, we started to meet with people that could help us put this project together.

1137
01:30:21,090 --> 01:30:25,252
This year, we're meeting with a designer who's going to take an entire year to put this together.

1138
01:30:26,531 --> 01:30:40,946
I don't understand how we're looking at the police station, the fire station, the high school, and we're saying, oh my God, the world is coming to an end today when this has been happening for 10, 15, 20, 30 years.

1139
01:30:41,687 --> 01:30:44,971
So the other thing I ask is, where's the plan?

1140
01:30:45,812 --> 01:30:47,934
We just heard that it would be five years out for

1141
01:30:48,899 --> 01:30:49,380
a new roof?

1142
01:30:49,940 --> 01:30:50,560
Where's the plan?

1143
01:30:51,361 --> 01:30:52,602
Do we have a plan in front of us?

1144
01:30:53,302 --> 01:30:55,224
Do we know how much it's going to cost in five years?

1145
01:30:55,384 --> 01:30:57,265
Have we started to map that out?

1146
01:30:57,865 --> 01:30:59,386
Are we planning for that?

1147
01:31:00,427 --> 01:31:08,773
Secondly is, if we're going to get 40 more years out of this high school, okay, what's the plan in 40 years?

1148
01:31:09,433 --> 01:31:10,414
What's the new high school?

1149
01:31:10,949 --> 01:31:19,676
Let's be visionaries and let's try to figure out how we can make this happen in the future for all of the people that are voting for you and all the people in this community.

1150
01:31:19,716 --> 01:31:22,098
Because I look at Medford as a gateway city.

1151
01:31:22,638 --> 01:31:23,639
Cambridge is maxed out.

1152
01:31:24,099 --> 01:31:25,040
Somerville is maxed out.

1153
01:31:25,440 --> 01:31:26,861
This is the next city on the line.

1154
01:31:27,682 --> 01:31:30,985
You want it to be Medford or do you want it to be Malden or do you want it to be Everett?

1155
01:31:31,565 --> 01:31:40,492
I think you guys really have to take a look at that and start planning ahead and putting your best foot forward because if you don't start investing now, it's going to catch up later on.

1156
01:31:41,352 --> 01:31:41,672
Thank you.

1157
01:31:42,673 --> 01:31:43,013
Thank you.

1158
01:31:46,956 --> 01:31:48,097
Name and address of the record, please.

1159
01:31:48,437 --> 01:31:52,440
Robert Penter, Zero Summit Road, Medford Mass, former member of this board.

1160
01:31:52,741 --> 01:32:08,032
With all due respect to the superintendent, I appreciate the fact that he was here knowing that in January that the application is out there and knowing that the school committee met, I believe a week before February 6th, it really doesn't give much time, whether it be for the school committee or even before the city council.

1161
01:32:08,433 --> 01:32:15,042
You know, and this is something I believe, Mr. President, that you should have been advised of in a joint meeting between the school committee and the city council.

1162
01:32:15,583 --> 01:32:23,635
While the council may have a lot of priorities and financial obligations to meet, that should be not an excuse or a red herring to say that's the reason why they didn't sit down.

1163
01:32:24,015 --> 01:32:24,916
I'll bring this out soon.

1164
01:32:25,316 --> 01:32:25,897
It's not right.

1165
01:32:25,937 --> 01:32:26,477
It's not fair.

1166
01:32:26,497 --> 01:32:27,438
It doesn't make any sense.

1167
01:32:27,958 --> 01:32:31,081
The job is here to deal with everything that the city involves you with.

1168
01:32:31,561 --> 01:32:33,543
Finances, education, whatever it might be.

1169
01:32:33,823 --> 01:32:37,105
And if you have to meet more than one night a week, wow, what a shame that would be.

1170
01:32:37,666 --> 01:32:45,452
Maybe if you met three or four times a week and you made the mayor become involved in all of this and make you to become involved with this, you'd have a better handle on what's going on.

1171
01:32:46,385 --> 01:33:01,477
Mr. Superintendent, you state on your document that you are submitting, you state, the school which is structurally unsound or otherwise in a condition seriously jeopardizing the health and safety of school children where no alternatives exist.

1172
01:33:02,197 --> 01:33:12,986
You go on further to state that the renovation that took place in 2013 regarding the science labs for which the Memphis City Council discussed on more than one night, I believe it was four times,

1173
01:33:13,880 --> 01:33:17,741
And as a result of that, part of that was because of recertification with the Commonwealth of Mass.

1174
01:33:18,341 --> 01:33:28,285
And further, the fact of the matter is that the building has not since then been renovated to meet ADA compliance standards and fire code standards that are needed to be current.

1175
01:33:29,105 --> 01:33:36,047
Now, how can our city allow that building right now not to go forward and have those requirements met?

1176
01:33:37,502 --> 01:33:41,345
That should be something that the school committee addresses on an annual basis.

1177
01:33:41,905 --> 01:33:42,766
That's an everyday thing.

1178
01:33:42,786 --> 01:33:45,308
You're talking about the safety of the children in the school.

1179
01:33:46,388 --> 01:33:54,714
You indicate at that point in time, you indicate that the fire code would be, it's approximately $1,200,000 to do an upgrade on that.

1180
01:33:55,475 --> 01:34:00,018
You also indicated that there is no way to close off the sections of the building

1181
01:34:00,489 --> 01:34:04,470
to prevent citizens to enter restricted areas during non-school hours.

1182
01:34:04,510 --> 01:34:08,352
You can go back to 1991, when I was sitting up there as president of the council.

1183
01:34:08,592 --> 01:34:14,974
And that was an issue that was presented to us as it relates to out-of-towners coming to Medford High School that were not certified to be there.

1184
01:34:15,354 --> 01:34:22,196
And in 2012, it was Councilman Marks who brought up the issue regarding the community schools on people coming in and out of the buildings.

1185
01:34:22,816 --> 01:34:28,058
And now you're talking about maybe having a program that cuts down the entrances, where and how you can get in.

1186
01:34:29,038 --> 01:34:37,343
You can walk up to that high school right now at any point in time, after hours, and walk into that building, and there's nobody there to check you in or to check you out.

1187
01:34:37,383 --> 01:34:38,144
It's totally unfair.

1188
01:34:38,164 --> 01:34:38,804
It's not right.

1189
01:34:39,865 --> 01:34:55,495
I can appreciate the fact that you might want to do all of these things now, but I beg the question, where has the school committee been on each and every one of these budgets, on each and every one of these years, especially on ADA compliance, especially on fire code compliance?

1190
01:34:56,865 --> 01:35:00,871
That's the thing that's necessary each and every day, that a child goes to school.

1191
01:35:01,172 --> 01:35:02,674
That's what you pay your taxes for.

1192
01:35:02,894 --> 01:35:05,959
That's what a parent believes their elected officials are doing.

1193
01:35:05,979 --> 01:35:10,926
They're making sure and ensuring that their children are protected when they go to school each and every day.

1194
01:35:13,885 --> 01:35:23,808
Mr. Belson further stated, with all due respect, that in next year's budget he's going to put a dollar amount in there for school renovations or school upgradings, whatever it might be.

1195
01:35:24,288 --> 01:35:25,849
We've been talking about this thing for years.

1196
01:35:26,489 --> 01:35:35,352
The new school building program had a 5% annual charge that the city was supposed to put in each and every one of those new buildings to maintain themselves.

1197
01:35:36,132 --> 01:35:39,493
And now, Councilor Caviello, Mr. President, it's well over a million dollars.

1198
01:35:39,533 --> 01:35:42,233
The buildings are less than, they're going on 14 to 15 years.

1199
01:35:42,453 --> 01:35:44,534
We're right back to where you were in the beginning.

1200
01:35:44,554 --> 01:35:48,375
That's the reason why you had to build new schools, because the maintenance didn't take place.

1201
01:35:49,255 --> 01:35:51,115
Granted, Medford High School is a big school.

1202
01:35:51,235 --> 01:35:52,515
It's a big school to take place.

1203
01:35:53,636 --> 01:35:58,897
But you've got three roofs, three brand new roofs on that building, and now you're looking at a fourth one.

1204
01:36:00,177 --> 01:36:04,458
The question then becomes, is the quality of the work not right?

1205
01:36:05,968 --> 01:36:09,250
Are we not checking out to make sure that the quality of the work is not right?

1206
01:36:09,650 --> 01:36:12,411
Are we just paying to have something done?

1207
01:36:14,212 --> 01:36:25,918
Another part that I really think that needs to take place to be discussed is the fact that, you know, this is such an important issue because this isn't a million dollars or two million dollars.

1208
01:36:26,258 --> 01:36:29,340
This is well in excess of your $10 million, Councilor Marks.

1209
01:36:30,080 --> 01:36:32,101
The school committee should be here sitting with you.

1210
01:36:33,393 --> 01:36:40,277
And you, Mr. President, I would hope you would call for a joint meeting between the school committee to consider as you go forward on this particular project.

1211
01:36:41,498 --> 01:36:43,339
You people got hit with this cold turkey tonight.

1212
01:36:43,619 --> 01:36:46,841
You should have been called ahead of time to have a committee of the whole meeting to discuss it.

1213
01:36:47,542 --> 01:36:50,543
It's before the bodies, before the public here tonight.

1214
01:36:51,784 --> 01:36:57,027
And to shut off debate on millions of dollars being discussed is wrong.

1215
01:36:57,487 --> 01:36:58,608
The debate was not shut off.

1216
01:37:00,289 --> 01:37:01,610
Point of information, Councillor Knight.

1217
01:37:02,480 --> 01:37:15,852
It's not relative to millions and millions of dollars, it's relative to whether or not we're going to authorize the school district to sit down and meet with the Massachusetts School Building Assistance Program to determine whether or not there are any grant funding opportunities that are competitive in nature for the city of Medford to pursue.

1218
01:37:16,695 --> 01:37:20,677
And if that be the case, that's a dollar, excuse me, Mr. President, that's a dollar amount attached to it.

1219
01:37:20,877 --> 01:37:26,420
Because the application before the school building assistance program, no matter what they allow, is going to have a dollar amount attached to it.

