17-304.

1585
01:59:21,082 --> 01:59:32,671
Offered by Councilor Lungo Kern, be it resolved that the Memphis City Council requests an opinion as to if we can vote to change our zoning one section or even one street at a time.

1586
01:59:32,731 --> 01:59:33,792
Councilor Lungo Kern.

1587
01:59:34,493 --> 01:59:36,534
Thank you, President Carviello.

1588
01:59:37,155 --> 01:59:46,322
This is something that a number of residents and I have been discussing along with, I believe, a few other prior councilors and

1589
01:59:47,050 --> 01:59:52,455
something that this council is beginning to discuss and have meetings on in subcommittee.

1590
01:59:54,056 --> 02:00:10,891
After doing some research with regards to how Somerville is handling their zoning changes, I read a few articles on it, and it sounds like they started their process about two years ago, and the last I read sometime this fall, they were still working on it.

1591
02:00:12,159 --> 02:00:13,520
They're actively working on it.

1592
02:00:13,560 --> 02:00:15,122
They've had community meetings.

1593
02:00:15,162 --> 02:00:16,863
They've had subcommittee meetings.

1594
02:00:16,883 --> 02:00:21,067
They've created a committee to review their zoning in its entirety.

1595
02:00:21,087 --> 02:00:23,989
It seems like they're doing it extensively.

1596
02:00:24,450 --> 02:00:39,062
Obviously, it's been brought up before that we should reach out to, I forget the gentleman's name, but reach out to the person from Somerville who is overseeing this project and get some ideas on how we can do it.

1597
02:00:39,524 --> 02:01:01,142
But in the meantime, we have a situation where a number of huge developments have gone up, a number of highly dense residential dwellings have gone up, whether it be Luminaire, we have one coming up on Middlesex Ave, and obviously a couple of controversial properties that have come down the line and have created controversy, I should say.

1598
02:01:01,162 --> 02:01:08,808
And it seems like the public and the public that have been reaching out to me and that I've been reading

1599
02:01:09,385 --> 02:01:16,831
discussing these issues are interested in developing, they're interested in not seeing empty storefronts.

1600
02:01:17,392 --> 02:01:30,363
Our residents are interested in redeveloping to a point where it's beneficial for the city and beneficial, how I should say it, beneficial for the neighborhood in a way that complements the neighborhood.

1601
02:01:31,024 --> 02:01:37,089
And what we're seeing with regards to, especially in the past, the number of variances that have been allowed

1602
02:01:37,597 --> 02:01:50,043
We're seeing a need for zoning change in this community, and we're seeing it, we're in need of it far prior to how long it would take this city council to review it in its entirety.

1603
02:01:50,403 --> 02:02:07,071
So my question, and I haven't reviewed any acts, and I know Councilor Knight just mentioned an act, so he can bring that up, but I'm looking for an opinion, whether that be from our city solicitor or reaching out to Somerville, some way to find out if we, as a city council, can review

1604
02:02:07,733 --> 02:02:11,955
whether it be a section of the city at a time, a street at a time.

1605
02:02:12,395 --> 02:02:19,179
We know of developers who are very interested in developing in certain areas, and we want to make sure that we protect our neighborhoods.

1606
02:02:19,619 --> 02:02:22,060
And you've seen that at the last few zoning meetings.

1607
02:02:23,461 --> 02:02:37,068
The public have been forced to have to come to the table and bring their concerns and questions and downright just opposition to certain projects, which is unfortunate.

1608
02:02:37,737 --> 02:02:45,478
You know, it does, whether or not zoning is going to be the solve-all, I don't think so, because we do still have the process of variances.

1609
02:02:45,538 --> 02:02:53,240
But with the new board and with proper zoning changes, I think we can make this a better process, and I think we can protect our neighborhoods.

1610
02:02:53,300 --> 02:02:56,880
So my question to our city solicitor would be, can we do this?

1611
02:02:56,920 --> 02:03:03,721
Can we sit down as a committee of the whole and discuss, I think, the latest project, Salem Street, for example?

1612
02:03:03,801 --> 02:03:07,002
Somebody else has mentioned Fountain Street is zoned apartment one.

1613
02:03:08,227 --> 02:03:15,629
Can we take an individual section of our city and say, OK, what is zone where, and this is the problem?

1614
02:03:15,689 --> 02:03:19,531
And then call that street or section in for a meeting.

1615
02:03:19,591 --> 02:03:29,413
I mean, ask the public to weigh in on what do you want to see in your residential neighborhood or your business districts that are right outside your residential neighborhood?

1616
02:03:29,453 --> 02:03:31,434
Because it seems like the administration is

1617
02:03:31,824 --> 02:03:41,810
pushing for housing, housing, housing everywhere, which is not great for our infrastructure, our schools, our traffic, our parking problems that we have on so many different levels.

1618
02:03:42,331 --> 02:03:48,694
And what I'm hearing from the people is we don't want to turn into Somerville, Cambridge, or Boston, these chairlifts we're talking about.

1619
02:03:48,734 --> 02:03:50,055
We don't want to turn into Boston.

1620
02:03:50,095 --> 02:03:59,301
We have more single-family districts or single-double-family districts in Medford than Cambridge and Somerville have, and people do not want

1621
02:03:59,718 --> 02:04:03,859
to see us turn into Boston, and nor do I. Our schools can't handle it.

1622
02:04:04,679 --> 02:04:08,860
Our streets, sidewalks, infrastructure, parking, traffic cannot handle it.

1623
02:04:09,300 --> 02:04:11,880
And I think zoning is something that we need to discuss.

1624
02:04:12,420 --> 02:04:15,681
Obviously, I have a long-term plan, but we need to discuss it.

1625
02:04:16,141 --> 02:04:21,822
If we can do it in a quicker fashion, I think we need to at least explore that option.

1626
02:04:21,882 --> 02:04:28,123
And this is one way that I think it could be possible, and I'm hoping that we get a positive result from it.

1627
02:04:28,467 --> 02:04:36,974
And we can take those sections of our city that are plugged hotspots for developers and really figure out what's best for our neighborhoods.

1628
02:04:37,554 --> 02:04:38,235
Thank you very much.

1629
02:04:38,415 --> 02:04:38,996
Councilor Knight.

1630
02:04:39,616 --> 02:04:41,818
Mr. President, I wholeheartedly support the resolution.

1631
02:04:41,898 --> 02:04:45,581
I feel as though getting an opinion from the solicitor is a great start for this conversation.

1632
02:04:46,061 --> 02:04:52,747
I also think it's very important for the council as we move forward to consider the impact that zoning has on our tax rate.

1633
02:04:53,837 --> 02:05:06,460
Because we have a bifurcated tax rate, we have the ability to equitably shift the residential property tax burden from the residential properties to the industrial and commercially zoned properties.

1634
02:05:06,520 --> 02:05:11,861
And now we're seeing a lot of use variances where they're going to try and eliminate these commercial and industrial properties.

1635
02:05:11,881 --> 02:05:20,903
And it's very important that we maintain a good stock of commercial and industrial properties so that we do have the ability to provide residential property tax relief, Mr. President.

1636
02:05:20,924 --> 02:05:23,004
So moving forward, I think that's a very important aspect

1637
02:05:23,669 --> 02:05:25,390
um, of zoning here in the community.

1638
02:05:25,890 --> 02:05:27,611
Um, council Longo Kerm is absolutely right.

1639
02:05:27,811 --> 02:05:40,896
Um, you know, when we go back and we think five, six and seven years ago when, um, the website, the real estate website, Reddit found Medford, um, the first thing that they said was unbelievable tracks of open space and natural resources and a large stock of single family homes.

1640
02:05:41,296 --> 02:05:48,899
And as we begin to develop and grow here in Medford, we're moving away from our large stock of single family homes and we're moving into high density apartments, Mr. President.

1641
02:05:49,319 --> 02:05:50,900
And in some areas of the city, that's okay.

1642
02:05:51,588 --> 02:05:52,769
And in some places, that's good.

1643
02:05:52,789 --> 02:06:01,575
And the mixed-use growth, I think, is an excellent opportunity for us to pursue an equitable shift between the commercial, industrial, and residential tax properties and the burdens that are provided to the residents.

1644
02:06:01,895 --> 02:06:03,976
But going forward, there are a number of issues that we need to look at.

1645
02:06:03,996 --> 02:06:12,101
And I think that one of them would be maintaining a good balance of commercial and industrial zone properties, as well as increasing our stock of affordable housing.

1646
02:06:12,442 --> 02:06:19,006
