1885
02:24:44,904 --> 02:24:56,229
So while the schools are built to hold 600 students, they are not built to hold 600 students where 100 of them need extra services in this and 50 of them need extra services in that, because those are extra spaces.

1886
02:24:56,670 --> 02:25:01,652
So this is extremely important to me as I have a third grader in that school.

1887
02:25:02,092 --> 02:25:11,347
and the largest third grade in the entire city at five classes and more than 100 students, just in the third grade, not including the ELL, not including the inclusion classes.

1888
02:25:11,808 --> 02:25:14,493
So this is very important to me.

1889
02:25:14,533 --> 02:25:15,655
This is very personal.

1890
02:25:17,504 --> 02:25:18,364
but just to get back.

1891
02:25:19,325 --> 02:25:23,447
So I think that we really need to consider this before we think about waiting for a consultant.

1892
02:25:23,487 --> 02:25:26,809
This is one of the most important things that the city council is in charge of is zoning.

1893
02:25:27,289 --> 02:25:29,910
And when zoning is going well, zoning is virtually invisible.

1894
02:25:30,010 --> 02:25:32,752
For years, the zoning in Medford was virtually invisible.

1895
02:25:33,292 --> 02:25:37,374
A lot of people went in, and they got their decks, and they added their extra parking spaces.

1896
02:25:37,414 --> 02:25:42,836
But all of a sudden, some developers noticed a hole, and they came in, and they're trying to fill us in.

1897
02:25:43,577 --> 02:25:45,778
And so now we're paying attention.

1898
02:25:48,452 --> 02:25:51,793
So we need to look realistically at what these neighborhoods can handle.

1899
02:25:52,113 --> 02:25:59,536
When we saw the traffic loads at the meeting that I attended for Salem Street, they recorded more than 1,000 cars per hour going down Salem Street.

1900
02:25:59,956 --> 02:26:00,536
Think about that.

1901
02:26:00,596 --> 02:26:01,777
That's a lot of cars.

1902
02:26:03,057 --> 02:26:05,098
A lot of times that traffic is backed up.

1903
02:26:05,518 --> 02:26:11,960
I tried to get to Haines Square over the weekend and the traffic was backed up almost to the Rotary at 93 on just a random Saturday.

1904
02:26:14,562 --> 02:26:16,503
The zoning there calls for apartment buildings.

1905
02:26:16,543 --> 02:26:22,468
Those apartment buildings can be three stories high and probably between 12 to 15 units.

1906
02:26:22,648 --> 02:26:27,732
Imagine them on every plot on Salem Street and the street would just be closed.

1907
02:26:27,772 --> 02:26:29,313
The neighborhood would be decimated.

1908
02:26:30,214 --> 02:26:33,616
That is what the zoning intends for that area as a whole.

1909
02:26:34,037 --> 02:26:37,459
And that may have been true when they created that zoning.

1910
02:26:37,759 --> 02:26:38,840
It's no longer true.

1911
02:26:39,481 --> 02:26:43,824
It's emergent that this council act to change that zoning.

1912
02:26:44,251 --> 02:26:46,953
to a more appropriate scenario.

1913
02:26:47,253 --> 02:26:52,697
What that scenario is, I can't say, but I can say that it's not apartments up and down Salem Street.

1914
02:26:53,037 --> 02:26:58,001
We also need to consider the load of those additional residents on our infrastructure.

1915
02:26:58,461 --> 02:27:00,983
Our police and our fire are understaffed.

1916
02:27:01,363 --> 02:27:03,505
Our DPW is understaffed.

1917
02:27:07,035 --> 02:27:11,257
So we really need to consider the quality of life also of people that are living in those areas.

1918
02:27:11,597 --> 02:27:13,858
What are their expectations when they moved in?

1919
02:27:13,938 --> 02:27:17,319
Because if you look at Salem Street, most of those buildings are one story.

1920
02:27:18,400 --> 02:27:21,241
There are some two family houses mixed in.

1921
02:27:21,721 --> 02:27:24,082
There's a couple of apartment buildings.

1922
02:27:24,322 --> 02:27:26,043
More of them are closer to 93.

1923
02:27:26,563 --> 02:27:31,005
These are not areas that we think of as high concentrated residences.

1924
02:27:32,328 --> 02:27:40,473
So we're basically trying to overcrowd this side of the city if we now target this street to suddenly enact the apartment one zoning.

1925
02:27:41,193 --> 02:27:50,899
We need to consider when we keep the zoning if our infrastructure needs can meet the expanding population that this zoning allows.

1926
02:27:51,600 --> 02:27:52,360
I would say no.

1927
02:27:53,641 --> 02:27:54,922
We can't support it.

1928
02:27:55,342 --> 02:28:01,406
We're not gonna suddenly be able to add one, five, 10% to our population

1929
02:28:02,085 --> 02:28:05,826
and be able to have enough police and fire to support that.

1930
02:28:05,846 --> 02:28:11,208
We know that it takes several months to train police and fire, but it also takes tax dollars.

1931
02:28:12,288 --> 02:28:27,993
While we heard that these new buildings will bring 100,000, or I think Locust Street said they were gonna bring a million dollars in new tax revenue, 490 families would bring in an incredible amount of additional needs on the city.

1932
02:28:28,447 --> 02:28:33,989
Even if they just had a small 10% children, that's almost 50 children added to the school system.

1933
02:28:34,389 --> 02:28:36,350
Can our school system handle that burden?

1934
02:28:36,390 --> 02:28:39,731
Can our budget handle the additional costs of those students?

1935
02:28:40,552 --> 02:28:44,493
So I urge you to immediately look at all the streets that are zoned apartment one.

1936
02:28:44,933 --> 02:28:46,374
Salem Street's not the only street.

1937
02:28:46,514 --> 02:28:48,035
Fountain Street's not the only street.

1938
02:28:48,395 --> 02:28:50,676
I'm sure there are pockets in other parts of the city.

1939
02:28:51,436 --> 02:28:56,278
My map is pretty hard to read out the street names, so I could only pick out the ones that I recognize.

1940
02:28:58,873 --> 02:29:03,954
This is coming and this isn't just something that is going to maybe happen.

1941
02:29:03,974 --> 02:29:06,475
This is something that is actively happening.

1942
02:29:06,955 --> 02:29:11,716
People are watching to see if this project at the old break pro is going to be approved.

1943
02:29:12,176 --> 02:29:22,278
And while it's great to see something different there as opposed to an abandoned building, we have to consider if the street can handle the load of buildings up and down the street.

1944
02:29:22,758 --> 02:29:23,658
So I hope that

1945
02:29:25,576 --> 02:29:33,199
you will take this seriously and responsibly try to change this zoning as quickly as possible before it's too late.

1946
02:29:33,519 --> 02:29:41,662
Because once those buildings are constructed and sitting on those sites, once those children are going up to the high school to enroll in our schools, it's too late.

1947
02:29:43,423 --> 02:29:43,803
Thank you.

1948
02:29:44,184 --> 02:29:44,544
Thank you.

1949
02:29:46,244 --> 02:29:47,765
Point of information, Councilor Neistat.

1950
02:29:48,245 --> 02:29:52,187
Any zoning change is a process that takes about 180 days, about six months, Mr. President.

1951
02:29:52,207 --> 02:29:52,487
Thank you.

